			<title>Lovecraftian Science</title>
			<link>https://nightland.website/index.php/journal/30-news/248-lovecraftian-science</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://nightland.website/index.php/journal/30-news/248-lovecraftian-science</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>If I posted very much about H.P. Lovecraft, I could easily drown the weaker William Hope Hodgson signal. Nevertheless, most fans of Mr. Hodgson are also interested in Mr. Lovecraft's work.</p>
<p>Considering the sort of discussion that used to take place on the Night Speech bulletin board, I think some of you will appreciate Fred Lubnow's <a href="https://lovecraftianscience.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Lovecraftian Science</a> blog, in which he frequently considers Mr. Lovecraft's works from a scientific point of view.</p>
<p>He has published <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_ss_i_1_15?url=search-alias%3Dstripbooks&amp;field-keywords=journal+of+lovecraftian+science&amp;sprefix=undefined%2Caps%2C146" target="_blank">The Journal of Lovecraftian Science, Volume 1</a> in paperback and ebook format, and is presently preparing Volume 2.</p>]]></description>
			<author>coady.k@protonmail.com (Kate Coady)</author>
