			<title>Awake in the Night Land: Grey Dog Interviews John C. Wright</title>
			<link>https://nightland.website/index.php/journal/30-news/235-awake-in-the-night-land-grey-dog-interviews-john-c-wright</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://nightland.website/index.php/journal/30-news/235-awake-in-the-night-land-grey-dog-interviews-john-c-wright</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><img class="float-left-blog-illo" src="https://nightland.website/images/journal-others-illos/awake-in-the-night-land-cover.jpg" alt="cover of Awake in the Night Land, showing the Last Redoubt" /><a href="http://greydogtales.com/blog/?p=436" target="_blank">Grey Dog Tales has an interview</a> with author <a href="http://www.scifiwright.com/" target="_blank">John C. Wright</a>, in which they discuss William Hope Hodgson's <span class="book-title">The Night Land</span> and <span class="book-title">The House on the Borderland,</span> and Mr. Wright's Night Land stories. If you're familiar with this site, you'll know those stories were originally published here by the late <a href="https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/107-andy-robertson">Andy Robertson</a>. They've since been republished in a collection called <a href="http://www.castaliahouse.com/downloads/awake-in-the-night-land/" target="_blank">Awake in the Night Land</a>, published by <a href="http://www.castaliahouse.com/" target="_blank">Castalia House</a>.</p>
<p>Mr. Wright's remarks are well worth the reading, as one might expect.</p>]]></description>
